title: TMAR F-Co. Commanding Officer (MEMS)
description: The Texas Maritime Regiment (TMAR) is one of four major components of the Texas State Guard (TXSG) which include an Army Component, Air Division, and a Medical Brigade. The newest of the TXSG regiments, TMAR, was formed in 2006. With more than 200 members, TMAR provides mission-ready volunteer military forces – with a unique maritime focus – for operations in support of homeland security, natural disasters and state agencies. The Maritime Regiment specifically embraces the unique structure and traditions of America’s Naval and Marine forces in preparing troops to carry out duties related to Texas’ land, marine, littoral and riverine environments. In the interest of creating the most effective response team, TMAR has forged working relationships with various groups such as the USCG, TPWD, TFS, and the LCRA. The Regiment‘s members are true volunteers who willingly accept military discipline, orders and training to answer the call to meet urgent human needs in times of peril or crisis. TMAR’s unique scope of missions include operations along the State’s hundreds of miles of coastline, its lakes and shorelines, and the rivers which define Texas’s borders – from the northernmost canyons of Texas’s Panhandle to the Gulf of Mexico. The Second Battalion Headquarters (2nd Bn HQ) currently drills in a Texas National Guard Armory in New Braunfels. The Battalion Staff has operational control of the sub-units, primarily five Line Companies. This includes admin, plans and ops, logistics, comms, and Public Affairs. Currently, Echo Company (E Co) drills in San Angelo. Foxtrot and Golf Companies (F Co and G Co) in New Braunfels with the Battalion Staff, Hotel Company (H Co) drills in Mercedes, and November Company (N Co) drills at an armory in El Paso.
name: Sean O. Weidner
